description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is Fixed Term for 6 months due to funding. If you are a SBUHB employee you will need to seek your line manager&#39;s approval before applying for this post. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic Assistant Psychologist to help lead an evaluation of Mental Health Day Hospital provision for Older Adults coping with mental health issues in the Neath Port Talbot locality.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Day Hospital Service provides to older adults coping with conditions including depression, anxiety, dementia, psychosis and trauma. We are keen to secure the help of an Assistant Psychologist to help evaluate this service through a variety of potential means including:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;1) Evaluation of clinical notes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;2) Learning from people in receipt of day hospital and their families and or carers&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;3) Learning from colleagues and partners about the impact of this day provision.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We hope that the post holder would be able to lead on the aforementioned under the supervision of a Clinical Psychologist as well as conduct a scoping of the literature and evidence base for examples of best practice in OPMH day provision. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder would be expected to present their findings in report and PowerPoint formats and should be aux fait with Excel and comfortable with statistical and service evaluation. Previous experience as an OPMH assistant psychologist is desirable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This project is particularly pertinent in light of Covid 19 and we wish to take the opportunity to pause, learn and modernise the provision.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Depending upon the project plan, there may also be opportunity for the Assistant Psychologist to develop their clinical skills in OPMH psychology under supervision.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amanda SwalesOPMH Lead Psychologist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amanda.swales@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kathy Williams, Kathy.Williams2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
